OOT_LENS.name: Fewer Lens Requirements (OoT)
OOT_LENS.tooltip: Doing things that would normally require Lens will no longer will, except for Treasure Chest Game and Haunted Wasteland.

OOT_TUNICS.name: Fewer Tunic Requirements (OoT)
OOT_TUNICS.tooltip: Most things that would normally require Tunics no longer will. Fire Temple past the big lava room, Volvagia, Fire Trial without silver rupee shuffle, and Water Temple central pillar still require Tunics.

OOT_HIDDEN_GROTTOS.name: Hidden Grottos (OoT) without Stone of Agony
OOT_HIDDEN_GROTTOS.tooltip: All hidden grottos will no longer require the Stone of Agony for logic.

OOT_MIDO_SKIP.name: Backflip Over Mido
OOT_MIDO_SKIP.tooltip: As Adult, Mido can be backflipped over from the front with a specific angle. It can be done with nothing, but logic will expect a first-person item to make it easier.

OOT_MAN_ON_ROOF.name: Man on Roof with Nothing
OOT_MAN_ON_ROOF.tooltip: Child can sidehop off the watchtower to reach this man, and Adult can jump onto the Potion Shop roof from the gate to Death Mountain to then reach the man.

OOT_BLIND_WASTELAND.name: Haunted Wasteland Lensless
OOT_BLIND_WASTELAND.tooltip: Turning this on may expect the player to cross the wasteland both ways without the Poe Guide.

OOT_DEKU_SKIP.name: Deku Tree B1 Skip
OOT_DEKU_SKIP.tooltip: Child is able to jump to the upper portion of the basement without going around.

OOT_DC_JUMP.name: Dodongo's Cavern Upper Adult Jump
OOT_DC_JUMP.tooltip: Adult can jump to the upper platforms in the Bomb Bag room, removing the need for a projectile.

OOT_FOREST_HOOK.name: Forest Temple Garden Vines with Hookshot
OOT_FOREST_HOOK.tooltip: Link is able to hookshot to the vines above the east courtyard using only Hookshot.

OOT_HAMMER_WALLS.name: Hammer Through Walls
OOT_HAMMER_WALLS.tooltip: Using the Megaton Hammer against a wall will cause Link to hammer through it. This can be used to hit some switches through walls.

OOT_VOLCANO_HOVERS.name: Volcano Item with Hover Boots
OOT_VOLCANO_HOVERS.tooltip: Rolling with Hover Boots next to Darunia's room can get you to the volcano without the bean plant.

OOT_NIGHT_GS.name: Nighttime Gold Skulltulas without Sun's Song
OOT_NIGHT_GS.tooltip: This will make it so that Gold Skulltulas that only appear at night will no longer expect Sun's Song to get, meaning you will need to wait for nightfall.

OOT_DOMAIN_CUCCO.name: Enter Child Zora's Domain with Cucco
OOT_DOMAIN_CUCCO.tooltip: Child can carry a cucco from the front or plateau of Zora's River and fly behind the waterfall.

OOT_DOMAIN_HOVER.name: Enter Zora's Domain using Hover Boots
OOT_DOMAIN_HOVER.tooltip: Rolling once with Hover Boots at an angle can get you enough distance to get behind the waterfall.

OOT_WATER_LONGSHOT.name: Drain Water Temple using Longshot
OOT_WATER_LONGSHOT.tooltip: Using Longshot, Link can hook to the torches at the bottom in front of the room he meets Ruto.

OOT_SAND_RIVER_NOTHING.name: Cross the River of Sand with Nothing
OOT_SAND_RIVER_NOTHING.tooltip: By backwalking across the left side, one can cross the River of Sand forwards. Going backwards, one can backwalk at a slight angle.

OOT_SHADOW_FIRE_ARROW.name: Enter Shadow Temple using Fire Arrows
OOT_SHADOW_FIRE_ARROW.tooltip: With a precise setup, it is possible to light all of the torches for the Shadow Temple Entrance with a mix of fire arrows and normal arrow. The timing is very quick.

OOT_KZ_SKIP.name: Skip King Zora as Adult
OOT_KZ_SKIP.tooltip: Adult can jump onto the fence next to King Zora and then jump down behind him.

OOT_LOST_WOODS_ADULT_GS.name: Lost Woods Adult GS without Bean
OOT_LOST_WOODS_ADULT_GS.tooltip: This bean can be collected using Hookshot at a precise angle after killing it with Bow, Din's Fire, Bombchus, or Longshot.

OOT_WINDMILL_HP_NOTHING.name: Windmill HP as Adult with Nothing
OOT_WINDMILL_HP_NOTHING.tooltip: Adult can jump off the small stone posts to reach the central spinning platform.

OOT_LAB_DIVE_NO_GOLD_SCALE.name: Laboratory Dive without Gold Scale
OOT_LAB_DIVE_NO_GOLD_SCALE.tooltip: Using Iron Boots and Hookshot, it is possible to obtain this check without the Golden Scale.

OOT_LAB_WALL_GS.name: Laboratory Wall GS with Jump Slash
OOT_LAB_WALL_GS.tooltip: It is possible to obtain this Gold Skulltula by jump slashing it, then jump slashing into the token.

OOT_PASS_COLLISION.name: Pass through Visible One-Way Collisions
OOT_PASS_COLLISION.tooltip: Some walls and gates, despite their appearance, only have collision on one side. Turning this on may expect you to know of these and walk through them. Some examples are the Kakariko Gate as child and the awning behind Impa's House.

OOT_DMT_RED_ROCK_GS.name: DMT Red Rock Skulls without Hammer
OOT_DMT_RED_ROCK_GS.tooltip: Adult can obtain the Gold Skulltulas on Death Mountain without the Hammer. The upper one can be backflipped into after spin attacking it. The lower one can be hookshotted or jumped onto from above to collect.

OOT_DEAD_HAND_STICKS.name: Child Dead Hand without Kokiri Sword
OOT_DEAD_HAND_STICKS.tooltip: Fighting Dead Hand as child with Deku Sticks requires all 10 if you only use slashes. This trick removes the mercy of fighting it with a sword.

OOT_BFA_MUDWALLS.name: Break Mud Walls with Blue Fire Arrows
OOT_BFA_MUDWALLS.tooltip: Blue Fire has the ability to break mudwalls. Turning this on will allow the Blue Fire Arrows to be logical for breaking these.

OOT_JABU_BOSS_HOVER.name: Access Jabu-Jabu Pre-Boss using Hover Boots
OOT_JABU_BOSS_HOVER.tooltip: By using Hover Boots, Link can backwalk off the rising platform while carrying the box to skip needing to kill the Parasites and Big Octo.

OOT_SPIRIT_CHILD_HOVER.name: Access Adult Spirit as Child using Hover Boots
OOT_SPIRIT_CHILD_HOVER.tooltip: Using Ageless Hover Boots, Child is able to backwalk off the Armos statue to reach the Adult side.

OOT_VALLEY_GATE_HOVER.name: Reach Gerudo Fortress as Child using Hover Boots
OOT_VALLEY_GATE_HOVER.tooltip: Using Ageless Hover Boots, it is possible to backwalk off the small pegs near the gate then backflip over it.

OOT_MQ_ICE_SCARE_NOTHING.name: MQ Ice Cavern GS without Scarecrow or Hover Boots
OOT_MQ_ICE_SCARE_NOTHING.tooltip: The Gold Skulltula next to Pierre can be reached using a precise jump.

OOT_MQ_ICE_SCARE_HOVER.name: MQ Ice Cavern GS using only Hover Boots
OOT_MQ_ICE_SCARE_HOVER.tooltip: The Gold Skulltula next to Pierre can be reached using only Hover Boots and somewhat precise platforming.

OOT_MQ_GTG_FLAMES.name: MQ Gerudo Training Grounds Lava Room Walk along Flame Circles
OOT_MQ_GTG_FLAMES.tooltip: It is possible to walk along and jump between the flame rings in the lava room. Footing is very tiny and precise. This can allow reaching the underwater rupees without Fire Arrows and Hookshot.

OOT_FORTRESS_JUMPS.name: Jump up to higher ledges outside Gerudo Fortress
OOT_FORTRESS_JUMPS.tooltip: Outside the Fortress, Adult can jump to the upper vines without needing to go through the kitchen. Child can do the same after going through the kitchen.

OOT_COLOSSUS_GS_NO_BEAN.name: Desert Colossus Plateau GS without Bean Plant
OOT_COLOSSUS_GS_NO_BEAN.tooltip: It is possible to hookshot the Gold Skulltula without using the bean plant, but the Leevers make it a bit difficult to do.

OOT_ENTER_JABU.name: Enter Jabu-Jabu with Head Collision
OOT_ENTER_JABU.tooltip: Jabu-Jabu has a piece of collision on his head that will trigger the loading zone for the dungeon. Turning this on may expect you to exploit this by using a jump attack, Ageless Hookshot Anywhere, or Climb Anywhere and Hover Boots.

OOT_JABU_BOSS_HIGH_SWITCH.name: Jabu Boss Switch without Boomerang or Climb Anywhere
OOT_JABU_BOSS_HIGH_SWITCH.tooltip: It is possible to hit the switch before Jabu-Jabu's boss using Bow, Slingshot, Longshot, Bombchu, and Hover Boots + Bombs. Having Climb Anywhere logical makes this trickless.

OOT_WATER_REVERSE_RIVER.name: Water Temple Reverse River with Hookshot Anywhere
OOT_WATER_REVERSE_RIVER.tooltip: Using Hookshot Anywhere, Link can hook up from the Dragon Statue room, and then hook through the gate blocking the river before it has loaded.

OOT_WATER_PIT_GS_CHU.name: Water Temple Large Pit GS with Bombchu
OOT_WATER_PIT_GS_CHU.tooltip: It is possible to kill the Gold Skulltula using a Bombchu with a precise angle and timing. This is only relevant if Climb Anywhere is logical.

OOT_SHADOW_BOAT_EARLY.name: Reach Shadow Temple Boat with Climb Anywhere
OOT_SHADOW_BOAT_EARLY.tooltip: From the Spinning Scythes room, Link can climb the fence at the boat shortcut and pop up on top next to Pierre.

OOT_SPIRIT_BOSS_CLIMB_NO_HOOK.name: Reach Twinrova using Climb Anywhere and Hover Boots
OOT_SPIRIT_BOSS_CLIMB_NO_HOOK.tooltip: It is possible to reach Twinrova without Hookshot by climbing to the top of the statue, then using Hover Boots and jump slashing to the gate.

OOT_ZR_FALLS_HOOK.name: Use Hookshot Anywhere to get past the Zora's River Waterfall
OOT_ZR_FALLS_HOOK.tooltip: Hookshot Anywhere can be used next to the shortcut to get behind the waterfall.

OOT_DC_BOULDER.name: Skip Dodongo Cavern's Boulder using Ageless Hookshot Anywhere
OOT_DC_BOULDER.tooltip: Using Ageless Hookshot Anywhere, child can hookshot through the small hole at the bottom right next to the soft soil. Doing this can get you past the boulder without blowing it up.

OOT_LAKE_SHORTCUT.name: Move Between Lake Hylia and Zora's Domain with Ageless Hookshot Anywhere
OOT_LAKE_SHORTCUT.tooltip: Ageless Hookshot Anywhere can be used to access the shortcuts in Lake Hylia and Zora's Domain, but the angle is a bit precise. Doing this with Longshot is trickless.

OOT_JJB_BOXLESS.name: Access Jabu-Jabu pre-boss without the box
OOT_JJB_BOXLESS.tooltip: By doing a jump slash and precise roll, it is possible to get through the door without the box.

OOT_TENT_CHILD.name: Enter the Gerudo Valley Tent as Child
OOT_TENT_CHILD.tooltip: The Gerudo Valley Tent is only present as Adult, however it's entrance is still there as child. Turning this on may expect the player to know where it is and use it for progress in Interior ER.

OOT_WELL_ADULT_TT.name: Enter Bottom of the Well as Adult with Time Travel
OOT_WELL_ADULT_TT.tooltip: Intended for use with Boss ER and Full Dungeon ER. This trick will allow an Adult Boss to be placed in an MM Dungeon in this location.

OOT_ADULT_GALLERY_TT.name: Enter Adult Shooting Gallery as Child with Time Travel
OOT_ADULT_GALLERY_TT.tooltip: Inteded for use with Interior ER. This will allow interiors where you cannot age swap with Child-only checks to be placed in this location.

OOT_GTG_CHILD_TT.name: Enter Gerudo Training Grounds as Child with Time Travel
OOT_GTG_CHILD_TT.tooltip: Intended for use with Boss ER and Full Dungeon ER. This trick will allow a Child Boss to be placed in an MM Dungeon in this location.

OOT_REVERSE_DAMPE.name: Navigate Dampe's Grave in Reverse
OOT_REVERSE_DAMPE.tooltip: Using Climb Anywhere or Hookshot Anywhere and Age Swap, it is possible to get past the final door of Dampe's Grave and then navigate to the entrance in complete darkness.

OOT_GANON_FAIRY_TT.name: Ganon's Great Fairy with Age Swap and without Gold Gauntlets
OOT_GANON_FAIRY_TT.tooltip: By using Age Swap in the child Great Fairy entrance, Adult can walk out of his entrance and then walk right back in to access his Great Fairy entrance.

OOT_GANON_CASTLE_ENTRY.name: Enter Ganon's Castle with Longshot Anywhere
OOT_GANON_CASTLE_ENTRY.tooltip: While easy, doing this can bypass a huge chunk of potential logic.

OOT_SHADOW_TEMPLE_STICKS.name: Enter Shadow Temple with Sticks & Fire Arrows
OOT_SHADOW_TEMPLE_STICKS.tooltip: Turning this on will enable Fire Arrows and Ageless Sticks to enter Shadow Temple in logic.

OOT_WATER_GOLD_SCALE.name: Enter Water Temple with Gold Scale and Longshot
OOT_WATER_GOLD_SCALE.tooltip: It is possible to enter Water Temple without Iron Boots by using the Golden Scale.

OOT_COURTYARD_FROM_GANON.name: Enter Zelda's Courtyard using Age Swap in Ganon's Castle
OOT_COURTYARD_FROM_GANON.tooltip: Exiting Ganon's Castle as Child puts you in front of the crawlspace to Zelda. This will allow Age Swap to be logical for doing this.

MM_LENS.name: Fewer Lens Requirements (MM)
MM_LENS.tooltip: Makes Lens of Truth not a required item for most checks, excluding Shiro (stone mask check) and climbing the wall to Darmani

MM_TUNICS.name: Fewer Tunic Requirements (MM)
MM_TUNICS.tooltip: Most things that would normally require Zora Tunic no longer will. Pirate Fortress Sewers and Pinnacle Rock will still require it.

MM_PALACE_BEAN_SKIP.name: Skip Planting Beans in Deku Palace
MM_PALACE_BEAN_SKIP.tooltip: Jump onto on of the doorframes to skip planting the beans, removing bottle for this check

MM_DARMANI_WALL.name: Climb Mountain Village Wall Blind
MM_DARMANI_WALL.tooltip: Climb the Mountain Village wall without Lens of Truth.

MM_NO_SEAHORSE.name: Pinnacle Rock without Seahorse
MM_NO_SEAHORSE.tooltip: Go to Pinnacle Rock blind. The Signs are your markers for turns.

MM_ZORA_HALL_HUMAN.name: Swim to Zora Hall as Human
MM_ZORA_HALL_HUMAN.tooltip: Swim around the back of Zora Hall to get there without Zora' mask

MM_ICELESS_IKANA.name: Climb Ikana Canyon without Ice Arrows
MM_ICELESS_IKANA.tooltip: With a precise hookshot postition, you can hit the first tree instead of using the ice arrows to get closer

MM_ONE_MASK_STONE_TOWER.name: Climb Stone Tower with One Mask
MM_ONE_MASK_STONE_TOWER.tooltip: Play the Elegy of Emptiness on a specific block to climb a certain portion of Stone Tower

MM_ISTT_EYEGORE.name: Inverted Stone Tower Temple Eyegore Skips
MM_ISTT_EYEGORE.tooltip: Using either hookshot and light arrows, or bombs for a recoil jump, skip portions of the dungeon using the central bridge with an Eyegore on it

MM_SCT_NOTHING.name: South Clock Town Chest with Nothing
MM_SCT_NOTHING.tooltip: Climb the roof with a precise jump to access the South Clock town Chest

MM_GORON_BOMB_JUMP.name: Bomb Jump Fences as Goron
MM_GORON_BOMB_JUMP.tooltip: Using bombs or a keg, use the Goron Pound to leap into the air and get damaged by the explosion to hop over fences

MM_BOMBER_GUESS.name: Guess Bomber Code
MM_BOMBER_GUESS.tooltip: Guess the Bomber Code for Astral Observatory.  There are 120 Combinations. (The Video Link is a backflip over him)

MM_CAPTAIN_SKIP.name: Guess Oceanside Spider House Code
MM_CAPTAIN_SKIP.tooltip: Guess the code on the masks you hit with arrows.

MM_ISTT_ENTRY_JUMP.name: Inverted Stone Tower Temple Long Jump to Death Armos
MM_ISTT_ENTRY_JUMP.tooltip: Using a precise bomb long jump, you can make it to the switch on the left side of the room, normally blocked by the wall

MM_HARD_HOOKSHOT.name: Precise Hookshot Usage
MM_HARD_HOOKSHOT.tooltip:
Using the short hookshot gives you logical access to:
- the Deku Palace Bean Grotto chest
- the Road to Ikana chest and tree

MM_PFI_BOAT_HOOK.name: Enter Pirate Fortress Interior using Hookshot from the Boats
MM_PFI_BOAT_HOOK.tooltip: From the boats, you can make a precise hookshot to a barrel

MM_PALACE_GUARD_SKIP.name: Backflip over Deku Palace Guards
MM_PALACE_GUARD_SKIP.tooltip: With a precise backflip on the fence, jump over the guards as human link

MM_SHT_HOT_WATER.name: Complete Snowhead Temple using Hot Spring Water
MM_SHT_HOT_WATER.tooltip: Use Hot Spring Water to melt all the ice instead of Fire Arrows or Din's Fire.

MM_SHT_STICKS_RUN.name: Access SHT Pillar Fireless with Precise Stick Run
MM_SHT_STICKS_RUN.tooltip: With a precise path, light the three torches.

MM_SHT_PILLARLESS.name: Snowhead Temple Skip Raising Pillar
MM_SHT_PILLARLESS.tooltip: Destroy the snowballs with fire arrows or bombs and then jump down.  A precise jump slash may help getting onto the platform.

MM_KEG_EXPLOSIVES.name: Use Powder Kegs as Explosives
MM_KEG_EXPLOSIVES.tooltip: Allows Powder Keg to be an alternative to bombs in logic

MM_DOG_RACE_CHEST_NOTHING.name: Doggy Racetrack Chest with Nothing
MM_DOG_RACE_CHEST_NOTHING.tooltip: Climb the fence and make a precise jump to get to the chest in the Doggy Racetrack area

MM_MAJORA_LOGIC.name: Fight Majora to Reset Time
MM_MAJORA_LOGIC.tooltip: Access to fight Majora logically counts as a time reset, as an alternative to playing Song of Time

MM_SOUTHERN_SWAMP_SCRUB_HP_GORON.name: Southern Swamp Scrub HP as Goron
MM_SOUTHERN_SWAMP_SCRUB_HP_GORON.tooltip: Use Goron's ground pound in front of the Tourist Center door to clip through the roof and reach the heart piece

MM_ZORA_HALL_SCRUB_HP_NO_DEKU.name: Zora Hall Scrub HP without Deku
MM_ZORA_HALL_SCRUB_HP_NO_DEKU.tooltip: As either Goron or Zora Link, jump up to the heart piece.  Linked playlist has both versions.

MM_ZORA_HALL_DOORS.name: Access the doors in Zora Hall using Short Hookshot Anywhere
MM_ZORA_HALL_DOORS.tooltip: Using Hookshot Anywhere, it is possible to hook behind the doors and open the doors behind them. It is somewhat precise but works with all doors.

MM_IKANA_ROOF_PARKOUR.name: Jump from Ikana Castle's Roof Interior to Exterior
MM_IKANA_ROOF_PARKOUR.tooltip: Jump off of a piece of rubble to the slope on the wall, and jump outside the fenced wall.  Walk around the edge to get to the other side.

MM_IKANA_PILLAR_ENTRANCE_FLOAT.name: Float from Ikana Castle's Roof to Entrance
MM_IKANA_PILLAR_ENTRANCE_FLOAT.tooltip: Float from the Ikana Castle roof to the main entrance of the courtyard using Deku Mask or Hover Boots

MM_IKANA_PILLAR_ENTRANCE_JUMP.name: Jump from Ikana Castle's Roof to Entrance
MM_IKANA_PILLAR_ENTRANCE_JUMP.tooltip: Jump from the Ikana Castle roof to the main entrance of the courtyard

MM_POST_OFFICE_GAME.name: Post Office Timing Game without Bunny Hood

MM_WELL_HSW.name: Well's Hot Spring Water without Killing Dexihand
MM_WELL_HSW.tooltip: Grab the water before the hand grabs you.

MM_ISTT_CHUCHU_LESS.name: ISTT Block Room without Chuchu Jellies
MM_ISTT_CHUCHU_LESS.tooltip: Normally the room contains Chuchu Jellies to restock your arrows and magic. With this trick on, logic can expect to do this room without the Soul of Chuchus.

MM_GBT_WATERWHEEL_GORON.name: Cross GBT Waterwheel Room as Goron
MM_GBT_WATERWHEEL_GORON.tooltip: Skip the first yellow turnkey with a precise Goron Roll

MM_GBT_ENTRANCE_BOW.name: Great Bay Temple Entrance Chest using only Bow
MM_GBT_ENTRANCE_BOW.tooltip: Light the four torches using somewhat precise arrow shots

MM_OOB_MOVEMENT.name: Walk Along Surfaces Out of Bounds
MM_OOB_MOVEMENT.tooltip: In certain situations, it is required to walk on surfaces that are unable to be reached normally.

MM_ST_UPDRAFTS.name: Stone Tower Updrafts without Deku Mask
MM_ST_UPDRAFTS.tooltip: This room can be traversed using Recoil Flips or Goron Mask instead of Deku Mask.

MM_ESCAPE_CAGE.name: Escape the Monkey Cage with Hookshot Anywhere
MM_ESCAPE_CAGE.tooltip: For Interior ER, it is possible to hook over the fence and land in a spot where Deku Mask can then be used to leave out the front entrance.

MM_GBT_FAIRY2_HOOK.name: GBT First Underwater Fairy with Short Hookshot Anywhere
MM_GBT_FAIRY2_HOOK.tooltip: The first Stray Fairy in a bubble can be obtained with a precise angle.

MM_GBT_CENTRAL_GEYSER.name: GBT Central Room without Zora using Fire & Ice Arrows or an OoT Magic Spell
MM_GBT_CENTRAL_GEYSER.tooltip: Using Fire and Ice Arrows or an OOT Spell, it is possible to sink down during the cutscene, then swim into one of the tunnels.

MM_BANK_ONE_WALLET.name: Bank Rewards Require One Less Wallet
MM_BANK_ONE_WALLET.tooltip: The 500-Rupee item will not require a wallet, and the 1000-rupee item will require one wallet.

MM_BANK_NO_WALLET.name: Bank Rewards Require No Wallets
MM_BANK_NO_WALLET.tooltip: All bank items will not require a wallet.

MM_CLOCK_TOWER_WAIT.name: Wait for the Clock Tower to Open When Shuffled
MM_CLOCK_TOWER_WAIT.tooltip: With this enabled, it may be expected to wait for the Clock Tower to open without a way to quickly advance time.

MM_WFT_RUPEES_ICE.name: Collect the Pillar Rupees in Woodfall Temple using Ice Arrows
MM_WFT_RUPEES_ICE.tooltip: The rupees next to Odolwa's door can be jumped to after creating ice platforms in the water.

MM_ISTT_RUPEES_GORON.name: Collect the Floating Rupees in ISTT as Goron
MM_ISTT_RUPEES_GORON.tooltip: In the room before Twinmold, Goron can collect the rupees by rolling over them.

MM_BOMBER_BACKFLIP.name: Backflip over the Bomber in East Clock Town

MM_NCT_TINGLE.name: Jump slash Tingle in North Clock Town
MM_NCT_TINGLE.tooltip: Jump off the tree and jump slash Tingle's balloon. Sticks will not work.

MM_GBT_FIRELESS.name: Great Bay Temple without Fire Arrows
MM_GBT_FIRELESS.tooltip: It is possible to traverse the final room in the reverse loop using Zora Mask or Adult Link with a jump slash.

MM_IGOS_DINS.name: Burn Igos' curtains with Din's Fire
MM_IGOS_DINS.tooltip: Igos' curtains can be burned by standing at the top of the stairs next to his throne.

MM_BIO_BABA_CHU.name: Destroy the Bio Baba Grotto Hive with a Bombchu
MM_BIO_BABA_CHU.tooltip: The hive in this grotto can be destroyed with a precise bombchu toss.

MM_BIO_BABA_LUCK.name: Bio Baba Grotto Lilypad Luck
MM_BIO_BABA_LUCK.tooltip: Hope the item lands on the lilypads.

MM_WF_SHRINE_HOVERS.name: Woodfall Owl Chest with Hover Boots and Jump Slash
MM_WF_SHRINE_HOVERS.tooltip: The chest can be reached with a tight jump slash at the end of the hover duration.

MM_WFT_LOBBY_HOVERS.name: Woodfall Temple Lobby with Damage Boost and Hover Boots
MM_WFT_LOBBY_HOVERS.tooltip: The lobby can be traversed by damaging yourself with bombs at certain points. Very difficult.

MM_SOARING_ZORA.name: Zora Long Jump to the Soaring Tablet
MM_SOARING_ZORA.tooltip: The Soaring Tablet can be long jumped to as Zora from the back poisoned swamp or from the Woodfall entrance.

MM_SOARING_HOVERS.name: Jump Slash or Damage Boost to the Soaring Tablet with Hover Boots and Bunny Hood
MM_SOARING_HOVERS.tooltip: Using Bunny Hood for extra speed, Hover Boots can be used to reach the Soaring Tablet with a tight jump slash or damage boost with explosives.

MM_LULLABY_SKIP_IRONS.name: Skip playing Goron Lullaby by using Iron Boots
MM_LULLABY_SKIP_IRONS.tooltip: By combining Iron Boots to not be blown by wind and Goron to roll up the slope, Goron Lullaby can be skipped.

MM_PATH_SNOWHEAD_HOVERS.name: Cross Path to Snowhead using Hover Boots
MM_PATH_SNOWHEAD_HOVERS.tooltip: Hover Boots can be used to slide off the slopes on the side and get across the gaps.

MM_GBT_WATERWHEEL_HOVERS.name: Cross GBT Waterwheel Room using Hover Boots
MM_GBT_WATERWHEEL_HOVERS.tooltip: Similar to using Goron, Hover Boots can be used to get on the water wheel and then to the central room.

MM_GBT_CENTER_POT_IRONS.name: Great Bay Temple Center Underwater Pot using only Iron Boots
MM_GBT_CENTER_POT_IRONS.tooltip: The pot can be broken by rolling into it and the Stray Fairy collected.

MM_GBT_RED1_HOVERS.name: Reach the first red pipe in GBT using Hover Boots, Bunny Hood, and a Jump Slash
